					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I've been thinking about this for a while... The idea I talked about in the previous post (a sprite character and a background character) could be implemented like this:
<br />
<br /><img src="http://www.nesstuff.kit.net/fighting01.gif" alt="Image" />
<br />These are the 2 name tables, with horizontal mirroring. The bottom name table is dedicated to the background player (although the bottom part could be used for something else, but I coudn't thing of anything), so that it can be placed anywhere in the arena without problems (even when jumping).
<br />
<br />The arena could be static (256 pixels wide), it could loop, or the slightly glitchy horizontal mirroring side scrolling can be performed.
<br />
<br />A few mid-screen split would be needed. The health bars would be static at the top. The sky stripe would move or not, depending on the arena. It could even scroll at a different speed than the floor, for a 3D effect. Then it'd cut to the second name table, adjusted so that the character stays in the right place. Later, switch back to the floor wich may or may not scroll.
<br />
<br />Any effects such as energy blows, blood, hit flashes, etc. would be drawn with sprites. Some minor flicker would show, of course. Once I thought about using a few sprites to fake background details behind the players, but I guess it would only increase flickering.
<br />
<br />Sorry for the babbling, it's just that I like to think about those things... =)</div>

